INDICATOR_NAME: Population in urban agglomerations of more than 1 million (% of total population)
SOURCE_NOTE: Population in urban agglomerations of more than one million is the percentage of a country's population living in metropolitan areas that in 2018 had a population of more than one million people.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION: World Urbanization Prospects 2018, United Nations (UN), uri: https://population.un.org/wup/, publisher: UN Population Division, date published: 2018
